A:/> C:
C:/> 
C:/> # xsend no args
C:/> 
C:/> xsend.app
Usage: XSEND <filename>
C:/> 
C:/> # xrecv no args
C:/> 
C:/> xrecv.app
Usage: XRECV <filename>
C:/> 
C:/> # xsend SERI not assigned (SERI=UN: by default)
C:/> 
C:/> xsend.app XTEST.TXT
XSEND: XMODEM Send
Error: SERI not assigned to a serial device.
Use AS SERI <device> first.
C:/> 
C:/> # xrecv SERI not assigned
C:/> 
C:/> xrecv.app TEST.TXT
XRECV: XMODEM Receive
Error: SERI not assigned to a serial device.
Use AS SERI <device> first.
C:/> 
C:/> # Assign SERI to ACIA, SERO still UN:
C:/> 
C:/> AS SERI: ACIA:
Assigned.
C:/> 
C:/> # xsend SERO not assigned
C:/> 
C:/> xsend.app XTEST.TXT
XSEND: XMODEM Send
Error: SERO not assigned to a serial device.
Use AS SERO <device> first.
C:/> 
C:/> # xrecv SERO not assigned
C:/> 
C:/> xrecv.app TEST.TXT
XRECV: XMODEM Receive
Error: SERO not assigned to a serial device.
Use AS SERO <device> first.
C:/> 
C:/> # Restore SERI to UN:
C:/> 
C:/> AS SERI: UN:
Assigned.
C:/> 
C:/> HALT
CPU halted
